ardour (1:6.0.0~ds0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New upstream version 6.0.0~ds0
   (Closes: #946989, #961479, #961732)

  [ Ondřej Nový ]
  * Use debhelper-compat instead of debian/compat

  [ Olivier Humbert ]
  * Switch http:// to https://
  * Update changelog (remove an empty line)
  * Add support for PT session import
  * Add mimetype support and categories to d/ardour.desktop
  * Fix a typo in d/README.source

  [ IOhannes m zmölnig (Debian/GNU) ]
  * Refresh patches
    * Update version-parse patch
  * ardour5 -> ardour6 renaming
  * Switching B-D to python3 (Closes: #942906)
    * Patch all wscripts to use Python3
  * Import waf-2.0.19
    * Add script to import WAF
  * Add patch to fix spelling mistakes
  * Switch from CDBS to dh
  * Add salsa-ci configuration
  * Declare that "root" is not required to build this package
  * Remove obsolete file d/source/local-options
  * Drop unused lintian-overrides
  * d/rules
    * Fix revision generator
    * verbose building
    * Include helper-snippets for buildflags and package information
    * Have most override-targets depend on libs/ardour/revision.cc
    * Drop the "--lv2" flag
      * It wrongly sets the LV2-dir
      * LV2 support is enabled anyhow
    * Fix dh_shlibdeps invocation
    * Add licensecheck target
  * d/control
    * B-D on libdbus-1-dev
    * Remove CDBS-generated dependencies
    * Drop unused ${python:Depends} from dependencies
  * Update d/watch
    * Automatically append a "~ds0" suffix
    * Use '+ds0' suffix rather than '~ds0' for repacking
  * Update d/copyright
    * Regenerate d/copyright_hints
  * Bump dh-compat to 13
  * Bump standards version to 4.5.0

